Class Main

java.lang.Object
javafx.application.Application
Main
public class Main
extends javafx.application.Application
Java Analog Clock. This is the main JavaFX class for our Clock program. Contains all methods needed to run the clock.
Version:
1
Author:
Ben Wallen, Noah Kamenick

  • Method Details

    • clockShapeCreation

      public void clockShapeCreation()
      clockShapeCreation() creates the clock using a variety of shapes. This includes the clock circle and the text around the clock -- however, it does not initialize the hands on the clock.

    • buttonCreation

      public void buttonCreation()
      buttonCreation() creates the buttons features on the clock. This includes the start/stop button, the setTime text field, the colorpicker, and the setCurrenTimeButton.

    • setTime

      public void setTime()
      setTime() is the method used for setting the time to what the user inputs in the text field This is accomplished by exploding the user's string and scanning it for the next integer. Formats taken are HH MM SS, and the more traditional H:MM:SS.

    • setCurrentTime

      public void setCurrentTime()
      This method sets the 3 hands to the current time based on time information provided by the ZonedDateTime object

    • secondHand

      public void secondHand()
      This method declares and controls the second hand on the clock. Furthermore, properties like stroke and color of the line are setup. The clock hands are controlled by an individual timeline, with keyFrames set at angleproperties zero and 360 - allowing for full range of motion. Animation set to indefinite. (Careful messing with this - this code can be difficult.)

    • minuteHand

      public void minuteHand()
      This method declares and controls the minute hand on the clock. Furthermore, properties like stroke and color of the line are setup. The clock hands are controlled by an individual timeline, with keyFrames set at angleproperties zero and 360 - allowing for full range of motion. Animation set to indefinite. (Careful messing with this - this code can be difficult.)

    • hourHand

      public void hourHand()
      This method declares and controls the hour hand on the clock. Furthermore, properties like stroke and color of the line are setup. The clock hands are controlled by an individual timeline, with keyFrames set at angleproperties zero and 360 - allowing for full range of motion. Animation set to indefinite. (Careful messing with this - this code can be difficult.)

    • stopClock

      public void stopClock()
      Simple method for stopping the clock. Makes use of timelines previously implemented.

    • resumeClock

      public void resumeClock()
      Simple method for resuming the clock. Makes use of timelines previously implemented.

    • start

      public void start​(javafx.stage.Stage primaryStage)
      Start function. This initializes the program and adds all parts of the clock to a visual window.

    • processCurrent

      private void processCurrent​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)

      event - is the event being processed

    • processColor

      private void processColor​(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      This method takes in an event ActionEvent object to set the current time when a color is chosen from the colorPick ColorPicker. That color value is set to the flowPaneObjects' background fill.
      Parameters:
      event - is the event being processed
